content.description: Really fun dyno problem. Start with smearing feet and jump to a slopey jug. This one feels hard while trying it but once you stick it it's not so bad. Pull through some jugs and crimp and find easier climbing towards the top.
content.location: Start on the right side of the boulder on the jug below the dyno hold.

content.description: Start on the jug on the right-side of the boulder. Make moves up the arete until you make it to easier climbing up top.
content.protection: Tricky landing because of tree stump. 2 pads, spotter would be nice.

content.description: The impressive, tall boulder in the corner of the Yorktown Plaza parking lot behind the old Cosi bread restaurant. This boulder has some nice climbs and may have first been climbed by Rich Shoemaker but very large flakes have broken off the bottom since. A bit chossy! There is also a slab climb around the left side of the boulder which i haven't done. For this boulder a walk off all the way to the left is possible but a bit annoying. I downclimbed as far as I could before dropping off a few feet to my crash pads.
